n%20%26quot%3Berror%20in%20judgment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20exact%20nature%20of%20the%20allegation%20against%20Marchant%20is%20not%20publicly%20known.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20CEO%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprimark-worlds-biggest-disney-cafe-hair-salon-photos-birmingham-fashion-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emajor%20budget%20fashion%20retailer%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20stepped%20down%20after%20a%20woman%20made%20an%20allegation%20of%20inappropriate%20behavior%20against%20him%2C%20the%20company%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20press%20release%20by%20Primark's%20owner%2C%20Associated%20British%20Foods%2C%20Paul%20Marchant%20has%20resigned%20as%20its%20boss%2C%20effective%20immediately.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EABF%20launched%20an%20investigation%2C%20which%20was%20carried%20out%20by%20an%20external%20law%20firm%20after%20a%20woman%20made%20an%20allegation%20about%20Marchant's%20behavior%20in%20a%20social%20environment.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENo%20other%20information%20about%20the%20allegation%20was%20given.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMarchant%20cooperated%20with%20the%20investigation%20and%20%26quot%3Backnowledged%20his%20error%20of%20judgment%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20release%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPer%20the%20press%20release%2C%20Marchant%20accepted%20that%20his%20actions%20%26quot%3Bfell%20below%20the%20standards%20expected%20by%20ABF%26quot%3B%20and%20apologized%20to%20the%20woman%2C%20his%20colleagues%20at%20Primrk%2C%20and%20the%20ABF%20Board.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20we%20have%20committed%20to%20publicly%2C%20ABF%20seeks%20to%20provide%20a%20safe%2C%20respectful%2C%20and%20inclusive%20work%20environment%20where%20all%20employees%20and%20third%20parties%20are%20treated%20with%20dignity%20and%20respect%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20press%20release%20says.%20%26quot%3BPrimark%20is%20committed%20to%20doing%20business%20the%20right%20way%20at%20all%20levels%20of%20the%20company.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMarchant%20had%20been%20Primark's%20chief%20executive%20since%202009.%20In%20the%20interim%2C%20ABF's%20finance%20director%2C%20Eoin%20Tonge%2C%20will%20take%20over%20Marchant's%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20am%20immensely%20disappointed%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20George%20Weston%2C%20the%20chief%20executive%20of%20ABF.%20%26quot%3BAt%20ABF%2C%20we%20believe%20that%20high%20standards%20of%20integrity%20are%20essential.%20Acting%20responsibly%20is%20the%20only%20way%20to%20build%20and%20manage%20a%20business%20over%20the%20long%20term.%20Colleagues%20and%20others%20must%20be%20treated%20with%20respect%20and%20dignity.%20Our%20culture%20has%20to%20be%2C%20and%20is%2C%20bigger%20than%20any%20one%20individual.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EABF's%20shares%20dropped%20as%20much%20as%205%25%20during%20morning%20trading%20in%20London%20after%20the%20news%20of%20Marchant's%20departure%20was%20shared.%20By%2010%3A30%20a.m.%20local%20time%20(5%3A30%20a.m.%20ET)%2C%20it%20had%20recovered%20to%20a%20loss%20of%20around%203%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EABF%20founded%20Primark%20in%201969%20in%20Dublin%2C%20where%20it%20still%20trades%20under%20its%20original%20name%2C%20Penneys.%20In%202015%2C%20Primark%20opened%20its%20flagship%20store%20in%20the%20US%20in%20Boston.%20There%20are%20now%2029%20stores%20across%2012%20US%20states%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprimark-store-tour-new-york-first-visit-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincluding%20New%20York%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Orlando%2C%20which%20opened%20in%20August%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20also%20launched%20its%20first%20US%20campaign%20that%20month%2C%20entitled%20%26quot%3BThat's%20So%20Primark%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20aims%20to%20have%2060%20US%20stores%20by%202026.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprimark-ceo-steps-down-after-inappropriate-behavior-claim-2025-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fd