problem%20ultimately%20landed%20on%20my%20shoulders%2C%20and%20that%20weight%20took%20some%20getting%20used%20to.%20I%20remember%20bringing%20my%20laptop%20to%20a%20friend's%20birthday%20party%2C%20which%20is%20something%20I%20always%20did%20in%20case%20of%20emergency.%20I%20later%20found%20myself%20sprinting%20home%20on%20a%20Saturday%20to%20fix%20an%20issue%20when%20our%20primary%20database%20went%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20product%20became%20fairly%20well%20known%20in%20the%20Web3%20space%2C%20but%20we%20weren't%20seeing%20the%20financial%20payoff%2C%20so%20we%20sold%20it%20in%20February%202023.%20It%20wasn't%20the%20life-changing%20exit%20that%20we%20were%20after%2C%20but%20it%20did%20give%20us%20cash%20to%20fund%20our%20future%20ideas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229ceb416f-7b4e-4878-aa24-e9115bfa877f%5C%22%3EAfter%20selling%20our%20first%20startup%2C%20we%20were%20completely%20directionless%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20went%20back%20to%20the%20drawing%20board%20and%20started%20using%20a%20system%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-find-good-business-ideas-2017-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edeveloping%20new%20startup%20ideas%3C%2Fa%3E.%20We'd%20spend%20one%20day%20developing%20a%20new%20idea%20and%20decide%20if%20we%20had%20enough%20information%20and%20conviction%20to%20spend%20two%20days%20on%20it.%20Then%20it%20would%20grow%20from%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20used%20this%20process%20through%20dozens%20of%20ideas%2C%20and%20most%20of%20them%20were%20quick%20nos.%20A%20few%20made%20it%20past%20a%20couple%20of%20months%2C%20and%20we%20even%20built%20some%20pretty%20impressive%20technology%20that%20we%20sold.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20several%20months%20of%20trial%20and%20error%2C%20we%20took%20a%20step%20back%20to%20reevaluate.%20We%20were%20innovating%20in%20spaces%20where%20we%20didn't%20have%20any%20expertise%2C%20like%20construction%20and%20trucking.%20We%20decided%20it%20was%20time%20to%20dive%20into%20something%20we%20know%20well%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbig-tech-interview-tips-google-meta-product-manager-mock-portfolio-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBig%20Tech%20interview%20prep%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2290c58b1d-1068-4e6a-9d4f-21d850320ce2%5C%22%3EThree%20misconceptions%20kept%20us%20from%20moving%20on%20to%20better%20ideas%20sooner%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20current%20startup%20is%20a%20hub%20for%20automated%20AI%20mock%20interviews%20and%20Big%20Tech%20interview%20preparation%20resources.%20We%20launched%20it%20technically%20in%20May%202023%2C%20and%20it's%20been%20growing%20since%20then.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20coming%20up%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-products-services-failed-discontinued-2019-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edozens%20of%20failed%20ideas%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20realized%20there%20were%20three%20lies%20I%20kept%20telling%20myself%20that%20kept%20us%20from%20moving%20on%20to%20better%20ideas%20sooner%3A%20%26quot%3BWe%20just%20need%20better%20marketing%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BThe%20product%20just%20needs%20more%20time%20to%20take%20off%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BA%20little%20success%20means%20we%20should%20keep%20developing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20used%20to%20feel%20like%20we%20had%20good%20products%2C%20we%20just%20needed%20better%20marketing.%20But%20when%20you%20have%20a%20good%20product%2C%20even%20in%20its%20simplest%20form%2C%20people%20will%20want%20to%20use%20it.%20I've%20also%20learned%20the%20importance%20of%20counterbalancing%20my%20excitement%20about%20a%20product%20with%20realism%20about%20its%20success.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20miss%20parts%20of%20Meta%2C%20but%20wouldn't%20go%20back%20anytime%20soon%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20used%20to%20come%20home%20from%20a%20day%20of%20working%20alongside%20friends%20and%20interacting%20with%20different%20people%20at%20Meta%20and%20just%20be